<br>
As for Celestial Healing, it's an expensive spell for sure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . You might try and visit the areas where this spell drops and get in pick-up groups in that area if you can't do it in guildgroup(s). Great Divide (Wurm Caves) might work this way.<br>
<br>
For your gear ... <br>
<br>
Earring: If you have about 2500pp and a friend of an Evil race (preferably Troll), you could try to acquire an Ivandyr's Hoop. I got one, and in the end it cost me about 1300pp ... figuring you can sell them for about 5k-7k, that is not bad. Otherwise Forest Loops are the best you can get at your level ... I still have one, too. Wis +6.<br>
Neck: Goblin Soulcaller. You can either hunt for this thing yourself in Frontier Mountains, or purchase one ... I believe the current price is around 500pp or so. Wis +5.<br>
Face: Upgrade to Velium Ruby Veil is the only easy option left, I think. Wis +8.<br>
Shoulders: I use those as well.<br>
Hands: And those too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
Wrist: On par with Bracers of the Reverent (which I have), so good here, I guess.<br>
Belt: Is a good one. I lucked upon a Girdle of the Diligent, otherwise I would be using this one still as well.<br>
Cloak: Hard to get anything better there. I only recently replaced it with some piece of Cultural armor.<br>
Boots: Mmm .. Crystal Lined Slippers in Crystal Caverns, Queen's Room is a good one, Wis +3. Otherwise try and get in an Efreeti group in Sol A, Nagafen's Lair. You'd get a chance at Golden Efreeti Boots, Wis +9.<br>
<br>
Arms, Chest, Legs: this really depends. I myself use Cultural smithed Human armor there (which I made myself: Erollisi Marr Imbued Field Plate; each piece provides me with Wis +4). What race are you?<br>
<br>
Also, what do you have in the following slots: Head and Fingers? You don't mention them.<br>
