Eannyil<br>
55 Cleric of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulashannavalrynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lashanna Valrynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(11/7/01 12:52:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hi everyone</span><hr size=1> First off don't feel bad about being lvl 50 and having never gone on a plane raid...my first plane raid was at lvl 49 (1 blue from 50).  As many others have said check the lanys raid calander (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.calsnet.com/lanyscalendar)">www.calsnet.com/lanyscalendar)</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> for when there are raids and try to sign up for a few.  Seriously if you have the time it's a great way to get better armor.  Usually most raids are always looking for a few more clerics. And as you raid more you might find that you prefer to raid with some guilds more then other, but that's all a part of raiding <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
